snippet.textDisplay: Tomorrow is not a guarantee to anyone. Besides Kobe's tragic loss, many around the world died leaving this world unexpected and unprepared. Pray God to strengthen the wife and children he leaves behind. What a beautiful wife and children he had. Let us morn with those that morn and remember many untold stories of beautiful lives lost yesterday and the days before. I will end with these words "Lord, make me to know mine end, and the measure of my days, what it is; that I may know how frail I am. Behold, thou hast made my days as a handbreadth; and mine age is as nothing before thee: verily every man at his best state is altogether vanity. Surely every man walketh in a vain show: surely they are disquieted in vain: he heapeth up riches, and knoweth not who shall gather them. And now, Lord, what wait I for? my hope is in thee" (Psalm 39:4-7). In all you do in life remember the Lord Jesus Christ  who came into the world to die for the salvation of your soul because once you leave this world without him, behold the tragedy of an unending existence that awaits everyman born of a woman.  My prayer and wish is that his soul (Kobe Bryant) was saved hopefully before he left this world (Luke @-20).

snippet.textDisplay: 我来自中国上海，是一个80后，小时候对于篮球的认知来自于乔丹，长大了是科比让我了解了什么叫nba，什么叫永不言败，科比就是nba，虽然我是一名足球迷，不是经常看篮球，也不是湖人球迷，但是每当看nba，科比永远是首选，科比在我心里已经封神，甚至超过了乔丹!在中国的新年中午我还在睡懒觉，醒来得知科比的噩耗，到现在都觉得不是真的，让我痛哭了一个中午，他不仅代表了nba，也代表了我和所有中国80后的青春，在此希望他一路走好，我们永远记得你，you'llall,ways rememberyou!
